content.description: Nice movement on this route that heads up the steepest section of the wall with positive hornlike holds.
content.location: Black-hold route under the fourth anchor from the left.

content.description: Some holds are deceptive, but mostly it's got good jugs. Crux is nearer the top with a bigger foot move. Holds can be kind of polished and slippery.
content.protection: Toprope only, no bolts or draws. Two-bolt anchor with two permadraws that you can move the rope to from another route.
content.location: Route with animal-shaped orange holds under the second anchor from the right.

climbs.name: Soup Sandwich in Seltzer Water City

content.description: The smallest holds coincide with the most overhanging section, but otherwise it's a walkup.
content.location: Orange-hold route that wanders between the third and fourth anchors from the left, and can be toproped from either.

content.description: Interesting sequence with nothing too difficult but avoiding a pump. More holds than its neighbor, but mostly smaller ones.
content.protection: Four bolts, the top three with permadraws, and a bolted anchor with lowering biners.
content.location: Orange-hold route on the farthest left bolt line.

content.description: An intensely bouldery start leads to easy climbing above. Not the greatest route setting due to the dichotomy, but it is slightly interesting. There's very little feet for the start if you're committed to not using the other holds, since the wall texture isn't great and smears don't stick super well.
content.protection: Four bolts with permadraws (quick link, wire, carabiner). The draws are a bit rusty. Two-bolt anchor which also has two permadraws.
content.location: Green-hold route farthest to the right.

content.description: Steep and consistent with smaller holds, but there's always a juggish piece of plastic to slap when you need it.
content.protection: Four bolts and a two-bolt anchor with lowering biners. First bolt needs a quickdraw but the rest have permas.
content.location: White-hold route under the farthest left anchor.

climbs.name: Ice Cream Sandwich in Martha Stewart's Handbag

content.description: Jugs, jugs, jugs! Big holds and decent enough route setting that it's consistently easy. Would be 5.6 but it's still a bit steep.
content.location: Purpleish hold route under the third anchors from the left.

content.description: Straightforward jug-pulling until the crux, a high foot step while holding on a two-hand undercling.
content.location: Green-hold route under the second anchors from the left.

content.description: Many underclings after the first steep moves, but it flattens out towards the top.
content.protection: Four fixed draws and bolted anchor with lowering biners.
content.location: Orange-hold route following the central bolt line.

content.description: Holds are plentiful at the beginning, but get rounded and slopy at the crux final moves.
content.location: Black-hold route under the second anchors from the left.

content.description: An intense boulder problem at the first two bolts leads to easier climbing above. Two left hands and a right heel hook should give you enough leverage to stab up to the next hold and then use all your core strength and positioning to maneuver up past the second bulge. If the hold (which sometimes spins) is facing a different way, it can be a much easier dyno move. It's all over after the second bolt.
content.protection: Four bolts with permadraws, bolted anchor with two lowering biners.
content.location: Route in the center of the wall with all the green jugs.
